      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNLEASH IN MIAMI (5) has a strong record this track and trip with four wins and five placings from 12 starts. Was out of the placings last time (29.98) at this track in a Grade 4/5, finishing sixth and beaten 6 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. ZIPPING HOPKINS (2) is generally an honest type in the frame at 29 of 70 starts but missed the placings last time when fifth (30.69) over 527m at Gunnedah. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Rates a winning chance on best. PROWESS (7) was beaten for speed from wide out but attacked the line strongly to place, 2.25 lengths from the winner (30.40) at this track in Grade 5. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Expected to feature again. GEORGE TARO (1) is always a threat when he draws this box.",
